## Early game

**Hellas** on Mars (Extermination) is a quick way to stock up on Morphics
from the very start of the star chart — the wiki notes Morphics have a much
higher drop chance on Mars than anywhere else, "making it one of the easiest
rare components to obtain" there despite the rare-resource label. Morphics
drop from Mars' enemies, so a Resource Drop Booster and Nekros Desecrate
multiply what you get per run. **Lares** on Mercury (Defense) is a fine
secondary stop if you're farming before Mars is unlocked.

## Mid & late game

Mars stays the best Morphics planet at every progression stage, per the
wiki, so **Olympus** (Disruption, Steel Path) is the natural endgame upgrade:
Steel Path keeps dense Grineer (and Demolysts) spawning across rotations.
Since Morphics are an enemy drop, a Resource Drop Booster, the Steel Path
passive and a loot frame all stack — more kills across more rotations is what
raises the yield.

